To calculate the Quick Ratio as of the end of the reporting period, we use the formula:

Quick Ratio = (Cash + Bank Deposits + Interest Receivable + Accounts Receivable) / Total Current Liabilities

From the problem data (End_amount as of 2024-02-05):

- Cash on Hand = 3,041,599.18
- Bank Deposits = 1,103,978.40
- Interest Receivable = 13,555.89
- Accounts Receivable = 10,537,836.59
- Inventory = 6,100,000.00 (excluded for quick ratio)
- Total Current Liabilities = 1,903,121.89

Sum of quick assets = 3,041,599.18 + 1,103,978.40 + 13,555.89 + 10,537,836.59  
= 14,696,970.06

Now, dividing by current liabilities:

Quick Ratio = 14,696,970.06 / 1,903,121.89 â‰ˆ 7.72
